subSection.paragraph:
The millipede family Paradoxosomatidae is among the most diverse and widespread globally, indigenous species being absent not only from Antarctica , which is self-evident, but conspicuously also from North America ( Jeekel 1963 , 1968 ; Hoffman 1999 ). The family currently comprises 1000+ species from 200+ genera, 22 tribes and three subfamilies ( Nguyen and Sierwald 2013 ;
Enghoff et al . 2015
; Golovatch and Liu 2020 ), being especially diverse in and even dominating the diplopod faunas of Indo-Australia ( Golovatch and Liu 2020 ), but only marginally populating Central and North America north of Panama . In contrast, the indigenous paradoxosomatid fauna of South America south of Panama is quite rich, highly peculiar and diverse (140+ species).

